Granbrix 5Lt.description: Granbrix upgrades the quality characteristics of fruits of all crops

Early artichoke seed Imperial Star.description: A green artichoke specifically bred for annual production, Imperial Star will produce well developed artichokes the first year from seed. Plants become 1 to 1,25cm tall and have an open growth habit. Each typically produces  1 to 2 primary buds, which average 3 to 4cm in diameter, and 5 to 7 smaller secondary buds. Perennial in Zone 7 and warmer, otherwise treat as an annual. Avg. 10,500 seeds/lb. Packet: 25 seeds.

Red tomato seed Caiman F1.description: This early maturing and high yielding indeterminate hybrid has a vigorous, open, compact plant with short internodes and good fruit set. The round fruit are large in size, 7.5 to 8.5 oz. (220 to 240 g), very tasty, and have an attractive deep red color. Caiman is easy to cultivate, and particularly recommended for unheated protected culture in the spring and summer.

Cherry Tomato / Tiny Tim (bush variety).description: These compact plants produce a good crop of cherry tomatoes Tiny Tim tomato plants will grow to approximately 30 to 45cm and will produce clusters of beautifully flavoured, sweet red salad tomatoes that are 2cm in diameter. This variety is suitable for outdoor growing. Growing tomatoes from plug plants is easy just follow the instructions in the growing guide that is provided with the plants.

Cobra French Climbing Bean.description: This is a really popular variety of French Climbing Bean that produces long, green bean pods which are about 7mm in diameter and can be harvested over a long period. If you enjoy French Bean Salads, this is the bean for you! French Beans are easy to grow from plug plants you can plant them in beds or large pots in full sunshine. A complete growing guide is provided with all plug plants.

Aubergine Black Beauty.description: Homegrown aubergines are an absolute delight. Easy to grow and delicious in flavour, finding these black jewels in your garden at harvest time is always a real treat. Aubergines are best grown in a greenhouse or polytunnel as they need the extra warmth. You could try them on a warm, sunny patio as well. They do well in pots give them plenty of compost. You ll receive a full growing guide with the plug plants.
